(1) The title to all
real and personal property, both tangible and intangible, of the converting
entity remains in the surviving entity without reversion or impairment;

(3) An action or proceeding
pending against the converting entity continues against the surviving entity
as if the conversion had not occurred;

(4) In the case of a surviving entity that is a filing
entity, its articles of incorporation or public organic document and its private
organic document become effective;
